I couldn't get Follow That Dream to display in full screen mode on my TV, i.e there is a black border completely surrounding the image. I had no such problem with Frankie and Johnny (I haven't watched Clambake yet). The issue may be that both Clambake and Frankie and Johnny are on single side discs and Follow is a flipper. I don't know why this was done as both sides seem to have the same content. Otherwise this is a good set.

Addendum: Clambake has the same issue as Follow That Dream, in that There seems to be no way to get the image to fill the screen. Maybe it's just my Sony TV that has the issue. I would be interested to hear if anyone else experiences the same thing.

I just love Elviv' films. I grew up on them. He has  comic wit that he (nor many others) never appreciated. He always wanted to do serious films.  His best is King Creople (serious), but the cute little beachy  movies are very enjoyeable.  His charm and wit can make any movie palatable to me.
